HEADWORD: Earthnut
<hw>Earth"nut`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A
name given to various roots, tubers, or pods grown under or on the
ground</def>; as to: <sd>(a)</sd> <def>The esculent tubers of the
umbelliferous plants <spn>Bunium flexuosum</spn> and <spn>Carum
Bulbocastanum</spn>.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>The peanut. See
<er>Peanut</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

